<bibRefCitation id="D232960A3BF75AE81EDE6BCAC0E68DF2" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal 1986b</bibRefCitation>
: 138.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C1B71A8EA74E27B447C84AFF02281BF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="A4664B479DC12D920C831BA890B83D84" authority="Hendel, 1914" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Haplomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Haplomyza</taxonomicName>
. Lapsus. 
<bibRefCitation id="9D9D6D9D64D182ADCE624666271A28F9" author="Spencer, KA" editor="McAlpine, JF" journalOrPublisher="2). Monograph 28, Research branch, Agriculture Canada, Ottawa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="869 - 879" refId="B255" refString="Spencer, KA, 1987. Agromyzidae. In: McAlpine, JF, Ed., Manual of Nearctic Diptera (Vol. 2). Monograph 28, Research branch, Agriculture Canada, Ottawa: 869 - 879" title="Agromyzidae." volumeTitle="Manual of Nearctic Diptera (Vol." year="1987">Spencer 1987</bibRefCitation>
: 878.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="397A184D4D51D70084431DAD7B1325D5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note">
<paragraph id="59CC0B300CEFBCF096DB2C15DB7C4A72" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
When 
<taxonomicName id="4EB02E3B355D6BF15ACEEC4A2174F2B1" authorityName="Melander" authorityYear="1913" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Antineura" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Antineura togata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="togata">
<emphasis id="FA6CEA334C934BD132C605452563C24C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Antineura togata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Melander, the type species for 
<taxonomicName id="0265F0DFA27FA02E8BBBDD58F57A2EE0" authority="Hendel, 1914" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Haplomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5710E7B53FD1BDA3E9A244F6EE2D6762" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haplomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was moved to 
<taxonomicName id="6CEAEFE0029D7F06BBB93655C9A99295" authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liriomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6B49C3175A9E24CAC296D48D5EC40DA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the remaining species placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4890A3E790FFB47F202882E57B09D5A9" authority="Hendel, 1914" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Haplomyza" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="74F6B76E8671498AC6D0BBAF6AC28BF2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haplomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were left orphaned. The name 
<taxonomicName id="9D9098B51F9A98FFADD36EBFDECFBE73" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplopeodes" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D146521FA6D1434EF012E144E95BCF69" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haplopeodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="32F9C504B39BC9725DCB38B4EE35A314" author="Steyskal, GC" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="767 - 770" refId="B267" refString="Steyskal, GC, 1980. Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 82: 767 - 770" title="Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="82" year="1980">Steyskal (1980)</bibRefCitation>
to encompass these orphaned taxa, which were found to represent a natural group. The genus occurs throughout the New World on 
<taxonomicName id="CFB0785BEDA2275DDB4DE538FD687337" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Amaranthaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EDEF61F8B7F3A4E07D6E8ACB65D3F9A4" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Chenopodiaceae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Chenopodiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CFFEF35220AA734C5BAF9D3BE62B5038" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Portulacaceae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Portulacaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B70F896EE8C796744EDF2B517EEC105E" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Solanaceae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
, producing short, irregular, and somewhat straight mines (
<bibRefCitation id="42C1FC07CBD3AA88E47C0E9D8A3A3997" author="Steyskal, GC" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="767 - 770" refId="B267" refString="Steyskal, GC, 1980. Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 82: 767 - 770" title="Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="82" year="1980">Steyskal 1980</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="0426AF7D7D573613FD7010047FBBB970" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal 1986b</bibRefCitation>
). One species occurs in Africa (
<bibRefCitation id="73926268C13DBB6FC0E2DB74CD62804E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810080503" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Entomological Society of South Africa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="322 - 344" refId="B233" refString="Spencer, KA, 1961. Notes on the African Agromyzidae - 3 (Diptera). Journal of the Entomological Society of South Africa 24 (2): 322 - 344, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810080503" title="Notes on the African Agromyzidae - 3 (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/mmnd.4810080503" volume="24" year="1961">Spencer 1961</bibRefCitation>
), but this was likely misplaced to genus. 
<bibRefCitation id="0885FA7D0B1B8A4E7EC59C3770610530" author="Steyskal, GC" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="767 - 770" refId="B267" refString="Steyskal, GC, 1980. Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 82: 767 - 770" title="Haplopeodes, a new genus for Haplomyza of authors (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="82" year="1980">Steyskal (1980)</bibRefCitation>
last revised the genus, and 
<bibRefCitation id="62B1EBC68BB6EBDA292009BB34A5339D" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal (1986b)</bibRefCitation>
last treated the fauna of the United States. A single new species was described from California in 
<bibRefCitation id="90627FAC280BFCCBB2E1AA450CF040B5" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4931.1.1" author="Eiseman, CS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 68" refId="B52" refString="Eiseman, CS, Lonsdale, O, Linden, J van der Feldman T, Palmer, MW, 2021. Thirteen new species of Agromyzidae (Diptera) from the United States, with new host and distribution records for 32 additional species. Zootaxa 4931 (1): 1 - 68, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4931.1.1" title="Thirteen new species of Agromyzidae (Diptera) from the United States, with new host and distribution records for 32 additional species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4931.1.1" volume="4931" year="2021">Eiseman et al. (2021)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D02DD83E1F994104E569339652425F04" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="E895DF5DA94F282EED3386D5F9C80D19" authorityName="Steyskal" authorityYear="1980" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Haplopeodes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haplopeodes" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7259B972A22231ECF552B4EABBE91CF3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Haplopeodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="78F2E48C9EE309520E819B42960D0022" authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liriomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E2F091453CBD8ACD8DF2C64C90AAD02B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they exhibit a strong reduction or simplification of both external and genitalic features, likely due in no small part to their minute body size. There is no stridulating mechanism, only one ors, dm-m is lost, the phallus is simplified and largely membranous, and the ejaculatory apodeme is narrow with little pigment on the sperm pump. Similar to many 
<taxonomicName id="74AC399099551D1B89061CB7DC1F0A7A" authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liriomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B64526C9D7237C7162E5A06135BE9B91" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the posterodistal margin of the epandrium has a single tubercle-like seta and the surstylus is small with few apical tubercles, but the ejaculatory duct is not pigmented and does not appear to be much swollen apically.
</paragraph>
